Deploy python flask app mongoDB Atlas on Heroku

link_1 : https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/getting-started-with-python
link_2 : https://stackabuse.com/deploying-a-flask-application-to-heroku/
link_3 : https://www.mongodb.com/developer/how-to/use-atlas-on-heroku/
link_4 : https://coding-boot-camp.github.io/full-stack/mongodb/deploy-with-heroku-and-mongodb-atlas

1. sudo snap install heroku --classic
2. heroku login
3. git clone https://github.com/<username>/<repoName.git>
4. cd python-getting-started
5. heroku create appName
6. heroku git:remote -a appName
7. git add.
8. git commit -m 'commit message'
9. git push heroku master
9.1 heroku git:remote -a appName
10. heroku ps:scale web=1
11. heroku open
12. heroku logs --tail
13. use link_3, link_4 to create:
    13.1. MongoDB Atlas
    13.2. Cluster in the Atlas
    13.3. Database in the Cluster
    13.4. Getting URI to connect MongoDB Atlas to Heroku and Flask-Application.
